<br />
<br />
if they were to add a frost barrier, a % chance to root is not needed, as we have falling star with an already % based root, AND we have the second cold finisher with another root.<br />
<br />
if you get lucky with seradon's and pop insta crit you can currently root a mob in place for 27 seconds at lvl 50.  <br />
<br />
the 25% hate reduction is noticiable.  especially when spamming CV.  You also have to consider other classes buffs that can reduce hate as well, so it has to be low enough that it will stack, but high enough to be noticable.<br />
<br />
I think 25% or 1/4 less hate is a HUGE difference.  if you were bound by aggro, then this barrier would allow for 25% more dps before you pulled it.  in the right situations thats huge.<br />
<br />
<br />
the % chance to snare at 25% is too high.  you can cast 4 spells in that 8 sec window and re-snare the target.  from the durations on our frostbite's we aren't meant to have long duration snares like druids.  so having a self buff that lets us basically chain snare a mob is probably not going to happen.<br />
However, putting it at 15% chance would mean out of 20 casts (40 second window) the spell would proc 3 times adding 24 seconds of that 40 seconds to snaring.<br />
<br />
basically i purposly had the % lower so that it would be a once per fight proc, especially since 3 dots at lvl 50 take at least 2 full frostbite durations to kill on average.  this would extend it out and possibly only take 1 if you use your spells efficiently.  This also has the added effect of randomly snaring your target, so if you do pull agro you have a good chance that the mob is snared and it will give you time to root it, de-agro or move back.  which gives the tank more time to re-establish agro from proximity.<br />
<br />
The %chance to stun is in there because when you're out soloing and some mobs have nukes, being able to stun them at least once per fight is invaluable.  the % chance to stun also helps in group play to reduce incomming damage on the tank, keep the mob in swinging range of the tank for proximity agro, and help stop mob casts in certain situations.
                  
		</div>
		<!-- / message -->
	
		
		
		
		
		
	
	</td>
</tr>
