<br />
Well, as far as the Flame / Force barrier balance, i think adding the AOE immunity to Force would make it much more desirable.<br />
<br />
It really doesnt matter how much mitigation we get, it would only make the difference between 1 or 2 hits at most, and it a hard group area or raid area, its benefit would be dwarfed by the damage and efficiency boost of the Flame Barrier, and i honestly wouldnt think many sorcerers would shift effectiveness for a tiny bit better safety, especially with the popular mindset of &quot;glass cannon&quot; that people seem to love lol <img src="images/smilies/smile.gif" border="0" alt="" title="Smilie" class="inlineimg" /><br />
<br />
Force: Its a force shield that blocks aoe attacks, provides some protection, and even protects us from our own attack's recourse.<br />
* Prevents AOE except when we are the target of the aoe.<br />
* 30% Increases Armor class<br />
* Removes Health and halves Endurance costs of our spells.<br />
<br />
This makes using CV safe if no healer can spare heals (but less damage), and lets us use our arcane spells more effectively, especially Shocking Grasp which we could perform safely w/o worry from the AOEs<br />
<br />
Frost:<br />
* 15% chance to snare for 8 seconds on each spell<br />
* 15% chance to stun foes for 4 seconds when they hit us <br />
(or lower % chance if its on each cast of our spells)<br />
* 25% less hate generation<br />
<br />
<br />
Perhaps that would be more in line with making the Force Barrier our &quot;safe&quot; dps option, with Flame Barrier being our max dps option, and Frost Barrier being our solo / low agro dps option, and Chromatic being our anti-spell dps option?<br />
<br />
What are your opinions on that?
                  
