<br />
The intent is a discussion on giving more flavor, making more choices on how to deal damage, that was pretty clear to me from the get go.<br />
<br />
Agro control will be needed come raid time, there are other classes that already have this mechanic in game.  (paly's give mele hate reduc, and a certain affinity cleric give hate reduc)<br />
<br />
If you ever played EQ2, you would understand this, thinking ahead is what this game needs, planning and management / ideas that will avoid problems that other MMO's encounter.  <br />
<br />
The idea behind the &quot;frost&quot; barrier is one of a defensive one.  The chance to stun/snare is for those times when you accidentally pull agro, having the chance that the mob get auto snared or stunned will prevent you from certain death in most senarios, and give the tank the &quot;TIME&quot; needed to pull agro back.  For soloing, we actually have the worst kiting ability of the caster subclasses.  Our snare's are the shortest durations of them all.  I dont like having to sacrifice dps to re-snare a target every 14s, but having a defensive barrier with a chance to snare/stun the target for me is kind of nice, and lets me focus on pumping out damage.
                  
		</div>
