				<div>Originally Posted by <strong>Illusive</strong></div>
				<div style="font-style:italic">
The idea behind the &quot;frost&quot; barrier is one of a defensive one.  The chance to stun/snare is for those times when you accidentally pull agro, having the chance that the mob get auto snared or stunned will prevent you from certain death in most senarios, and give the tank the &quot;TIME&quot; needed to pull agro back.  For soloing, we actually have the worst kiting ability of the caster subclasses.  Our snare's are the shortest durations of them all.  I dont like having to sacrifice dps to re-snare a target every 14s, but having a defensive barrier with a chance to snare/stun the target for me is kind of nice, and lets me focus on pumping out damage.</div>
			
		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>
</div>
<br />
Our snare/root does not break on damage. It doesnt matter if you have a 60 second root if it breaks with the first damage received (Ive tested few other classes, there is a reason why I like Sorcerer the most). Both, snare and root deals damage. So recasting them does not prevent you from dealing damage.<br />
<br />
I hope you are not saying you dont like to play a one button class but when you actually need to use 3 buttons to kite you complain that it should be made that you only need one button. Thats not what you are requesting, correct?<br />
<br />
You have spells to root (snare is in my opinion useless for aggro management because I dont have the space when it gets tough). You have a ward which saves you from the first hit. I dont like to get more auto play the game but this may be my personal choice. Unreliable root, by the way, is in the case of aggro loss almost the same as no root. We have reliable tools with the option to be used or not. Thats the direction I like for the class.
                  
