	<td class="alt1" id="td_post_1169471">
	
		
		<!-- message -->
		<div id="post_message_1169471">
                  
                  <div style="margin:20px; margin-top:5px; ">
	<div class="smallfont" style="margin-bottom:2px">Quote:</div>
	<table cellpadding="6" cellspacing="0" border="0" width="100%">
	<tr>
		<td class="alt2" style="border:1px inset">
			
				<div>Originally Posted by <strong>EmiliaSEB</strong></div>
				<div style="font-style:italic">Jhorry your ideas are stupidly overpowered , and i mean <font color="Red"><b>STUPIDLY OVERPOWERED.</b></font><br />
<br />
But the &quot;various Flavored buffs&quot; are nice (but overpowered)<br />
<br />
Still the biggest problem is that if we make shields too good and  &quot;shield dancing&quot; possible.<br />
We will end up with pseudo-stances and stance-dance. Fuck that.<br />
<br />
If you want my opinion, Fire Barrier should be a &quot;standart 24/7 sorcerer selfbuff&quot;.<br />
<br />
After that, yes you could add 2 or 3 special '&quot;extra buffs&quot; depending on the situation :<br />
Force Shield : 15% Rune,  50% Manashield<br />
Frost Shield : -25% Aggro +30% Manacost<br />
Chaos Shield : +50% Dmg  +100% Manacost</div>
			
		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>
</div>
<br />
Well, i do have at least a few minutes to respond as it turns out, waiting for my ride lol...<br />
<br />
<br />
I dont mean to be critical, but you are stating that some of my shields are over powdered, but your suggesting adding a stance that increases our dps by 50% while doubling energy cost? That is twice the amount of the psionicist's stance, and theirs still doesnt alow them to come close to the current sorcerer dps according to many people on the varrious forums (though i have no personal experience or reliable sources to support this)<br />
<br />
The psionicist's is a 25% damage boost on all abilities for a 50% increase in energy cost, to help them deal more spike damage when needed, while sorcerers can already deal much better spike damage than the psionicist even while they use this stance.<br />
<br />
The +50% dps would really overpower a sorcerer's spike dps by comparison to all of the other casters imo, though it would be interesting to test it in the field.<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
Basically, the deal with the shields vs stances is shields would be more of a &quot;mid-term decision.&quot;<br />
<br />
<br />
Stances are a short term decision, you decide if for the next 8 seconds or so if you want to be offensive, defensive, accurate, ect.., as you will have the time to wait before you can swap out of a stance. Bard songs fit in here as well.<br />
<br />
Short term decisions can swap in the midst of a fight.<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
Sorcerer's Barriers would be a mid term decision, you decide if you will need to be A) spike dps B) efficient and aoe protected dps C)low-hate generating dps D) spell-proof dps, that was for my original example. With a large energy cost, you would not want to do this often, so this choice would at least last for the duration of a fight. Necromancer's minions fit in here, or adjusting grafts on the abomination.<br />
<br />
Mid Term decisions can swap inbetween fights.<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
Long term decisions are like the necromancer's wraith or lich form, or the shaman's totems, or the cleric's affinities, these can only be swaped (if even alowed) by some time investment, and certainly cannot<br />
<br />
Long Term decisions can (sometimes) be swapped via an extended period of time.<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
So, in my oppinion you certainly would not be stance dancing as a sorcerer, but maybe adjusting your play style inbetween a fight to match your group.<br />
<br />
<br />
Got a tank that is really not holding agro well? You can just cast less, or you could toss on Frost Barrier and dps safely at a higher dps.<br />
<br />
Got a group that is really light on heals? In a tight area where getting range is dangerous? Might want to use Force Barrier for a few fights to be on the safe side.<br />
<br />
Fighting a boss mob that is primarily spell based? Chromatic Barrier might be a wise choice.<br />
<br />
Fighting a normal mob or boss mob w/o anything to crazy and your tank knows what he's doing? Go for full dps with Flame Barrier.<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
I think we would still use Flame Barrier at least 75% of the time, as hopefully most tanks know what they are doing, most fights wont be AOE intensive w/o you being able to range it, and most spell caster mobs wont be too brutal i assume.<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
Basically, you want the sorcerer to be able to adapt to a situation that they are in and still function well, just not have to adapt CONSTANTLY with the (at least to me) annoying idea of stance dancing.<br />
<br />
That is one reason i dont like playing Bloodmage, is swaping stances at the right time can make or break a good BMG.<br />
<br />
Yes, you can adapt with just how you play, such as simply greatly lowering your dps to not steal agro, or jousting way out of range for a very wide aoe, or just taking some hits to the face while soloing, but I personally like having the opton of deciding &quot;how&quot; i want my character to focus while he fights.<br />
<br />
I personally enjoy having some ability to &quot;swing&quot; my character towards a particular focus with a stance. If i want him to be subtle, Frost, survive, Force, demolish, Flame, focus on spell prevention, Chromatic.<br />
<br />
I could adjust my play style for either, but it still isnt as effective as if i had a specific &quot;focus&quot; for each individual play tactic.
                  
		</div>
