</div>
QFE<br />
<br />
This is a very good way of summerizing how Illusive and i debate issues.<br />
<br />
While we both agree on a common idea of &quot;more, diverse ways to accomplish a common goal is a good thing usually&quot;, we both have differing ideas of how this can be implemented. <br />
<br />
The common goal of all classes being being &quot;beat the encounter with as little death as possible&quot; lol <img src="images/smilies/smile.gif" border="0" alt="" title="Smilie" class="inlineimg" /><br />
<br />
(although i dont know if necromancers wouldnt cheer for a few slain allies for some more corpse rituals 0_o )<br />
<br />
By mixing and matching our ideas, stating how, why, and whats wrong or right with our ideas, and compromising in some areas, we can come up with some very good, stable ideas.<br />
<br />
Example:<br />
<br />
Originally i was really for the 75% agro reduction, but after hearing his argument about how just a 25% agro reduction is very viable, i readusted my views on it, and decided a 25-50% agro reduction would be very useful in some situations.<br />
<br />
He also readjusted his views on the 4 second 15% trigger chance off of spell cast stun on his concept of the Frost form to a lower trigger, lower duration stun, as stuns can be brutally out of balanced if you can get enough stuns to lock a mob down indefniately, basically taking out any need for healing/tanking.<br />
<br />
<br />
So, as we progress in this and future posts, please try to be constructive.<br />
<br />
No need to use profanities or degrade another person's idea as &quot;stupid,&quot; but instead focus on what you think would be beneficial for the game and the class w/o taking away from the (subjective) fun and enjoyment of it.
                  
