In eq2, wizards needed 3 forms of hate reduction (from 3 different classes) and at least 2 forms of hate increasers on the MT in order to deal the dps they were intended to deal. (troubador / paly or guardian / coercer, MT needed coercer / dirge for hate gain)  basically the wizard is gimped in dps unless the raid has the 4 classes and set up in the right group.  A solo wizard with no hate reduction is going to top out at 1400 dps, slap on 3 hate reducing classes and they can exceed 3k.  <br />
<br />
My concearn is that in vanguard, we deal massive burst dps with CV, and with no personal way to reduce the hate in % we are going to be reliant on a peace affinity cleric being on the raid to max dps or we are forced to deal crap dps because we pull agro and wipe raid.<br />
<br />
Why should we be gimped in DPS when one class isn't there or doesn't show up on a raid?  I freakin hated that with a passion in EQ2 (took 3 classes so it was even worse)<br />
<br />
Point being our job is to deal dps, having adiquate means to ditch hate is part of being a dps class, without a % based hate reducer, how do you plan to shrug off 50k cv crits? wait for 10 seconds and do nothing?<br />
