                  Thanks for reposting.<br />
<br />
I think your proposal is to complex to implement but its a nice idea.<br />
I think the countering itself needs to stay lean. The issue is, you need to recognize the cast then recognize the spell, take a decision and push a button in 4 seconds or less all together. All that, needs to be done in between all the other tasks that need to be done during the fight. <br />
<br />
I join your hope that counter spelling really makes, some time in the future, a difference in a fight. Doesnt matter if its through additional dps, reduced damage on the group, healing or CC prevention (heal counter dont need to do damage, Ive seen mob heals which restored HP worth of 20 second fighting time and I have seen this heals getting countered).<br />
<br />
btw: how far did you played Sorcerer in Vanguard?
                  
